main event: Radar contact and visual sighting of an unidentified flying object in the Pacific Ocean on May 28, 1963.
interesting points: The object was detected on air-intercept radar and observed visually by 6 crewmembers.
The object appeared as a slow-moving trail of an unidentified number of objects.
The object was silver in color and leaving contrails that blended into one.
The object was tracked for 3 minutes, heading west at an estimated altitude of 62,000 feet.
The sighting was reported to various military and intelligence agencies, including PACAF, CINCPAC, and DIA-CTIC.
sighted object: Slow-moving trail of unidentified objects, silver in color with contrails
photographs: No photographs included in the report
